{"word":"εἰρεσία","slug":"εἰρεσία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εἰρεσία</b></el> <el>(εἰρεσία, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐρέσσω'><el>ἐρέσσω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>rowing</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: —<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>εἰρ. πτερῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in collective sense, <i>the rowers, oarsmen</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>remigium</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a boat-song</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}